description:
Known to her female compatriots, the Sinsationals as "M" or affectionately, and jokingly, as Mammazonia, the Amazon warrior's origins are steeped in mystery.

All that is known about M is that she hails from a mythical island full of warrior women who've been trained for thousands of years in all manners of combat, both armed and unarmed. M was exiled from her home because of her perceived weakness in the form of "being merciful". Accused of her queen-mother of not being able to lead her sisters in battle because of this weakness, she was cast out of her island home and into the shores of Infinity City.

She is super-strong, super-fast, has a high level of invulnerability, is highly trained in armed and unarmed combat and her leadership skills are exemplary.
name: M

description:
Origin

Melchior is an inhabitant of a higher plane of existence known as the Brilliant City. Powerful humanoids existed in this city, pure, enlightened, clean and filled with knowledge and an a idealism many other realities could only hope to aspire to.

Creation

Melchior is a Marvel comics character, created for the X-Man series by writers Warren Ellis and Steven Grant and artist Ariel Olivetti. Melchior first appears in X-Man #67 - Shockwave: part one: Infinities of Evil

Character Evolution

Melchior is a supporting character in the X-Man series, most notably the arcs Shockwave and Fearful Symmetries.

Major Story Arcs

Shockwave

Melchior, an inhabitant of the the Brilliant City is conversing with his peers, his friend Qabiri insists that outsides present a very real and future threat to their chaste and pure way of living and existence.

Melchior strongly opposed the arrival of Nate Grey in the Brilliant City. As well as objecting to the return of fellow Brilliant City natives Qabiri and Idris, saying that them leaving the Brilliant City and being exposed to the multiverse had made them impure and unfit to remain in the Brilliant City.

Eventually Melchior, like all other inhabitants of the Brilliant City, lay humbled by Nate Grey who proved to them that they are not the supreme beings they thought they were. Nate showed that the Brilliant City, which now lay in ruin, and its inhabitants where, to the Higher Gods, less than ants.

Powers and Abilities

Melchior is extremely powerful, possessing extremely powerful energy manipulation powers. Extremely durable and robust, Melchior could withstand all manner of physical and energy attacks. An inhabitant of the the Brilliant City, physiologically Melchior is many multitudes superior to normal human beings. Melchior is long lived and essentially immortal, having existed for eons. Melchior peoples have even been described as unfathomable. Melchior possesses super human levels of durability, power, resilience and durability, and he can generate and manipulate potent and massive amounts of energy, enough to destroy worlds. He can travel dimensions, read minds, traverse through realities at her will, form powerful force fields, and sense other life forms. Melchior can fly under his own power and exist and remain unaffected by the void of outer space.

description: The only one with martial arts experience. He thinks of himself as the strongest member of the group and his team mates would tend to agree. He often disagrees with El Gladiator and it's not always because he has a better plan. He picks on Dr. Pantera for being overweight and - in his eyes - the weakest and slowest member of the team. He's the complete opposite of a vegetarian, he loves plants so much he only eats meat.
name: King Karateca

description: The Red Demon is a member of the Luchadores 5, the Lucha Libre team that rids the streets of East L.A. of werewolves and Tiki warriors. He's the smooth talker of the team, his snappy dress sense gets him the ladies even though he's wearing the - not that great looking - Lucha Libre mask. He doesn't hang on to the ladies he picks up.
name: Red Demon

description: Diablo Loco smokes sigars and dons the red and yellow Lucha Libre mask. He still lives with his mother.
name: Diablo Loco

description: Doctor Pantara is married, overweight and wears Harvard sweatshirts. His Lucha Libre mask has a leopard print design. His wife is against his crime fighting career, she just wants to have a baby. He gets picked on by some of the other team members for being the - perceived - weakest member of the group.
name: Dr. Pantera

description:
El Gladiator is considered to be the leader of the Lucadores Five, even though he garners little respect from his team. He's the self appointed defender of East L.A. Protecting the city is his main occupation since his -adoptive- parents support him. As a result he is a staunch critic of any team member holding a job. He also disapproves of any Luchadores having a girlfriend - not because he is single himself, as some mean spirited gossipers would have it, but because he strongly believes that these relationships weaken the gang.

He likes to sleep in late and has a weakness for afternoon TV shows. He drives a Pontiac Firebird, which has seen better days and claims that his understanding of the world is based on a complex philosophy of his own, too complex for anyone else to grasp. He contends that he is of Aztec origin and displays an ancient medal to back his claim. King Karateka says he saw El Gladiator purchase it a the 99 cents only store.
name: El Gladiator
